.NET Framework 3.5.name: SDK_Base
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: Abstract superclass that defines that a particular class is an SDK.
.NET Framework 3.5.remarks: This is an abstract class to mark all different SDK endpoints with. This is used to allow for type safety when talking about 'an SDK' instead of one of the different endpoints (System, Boundaries, Headset, Controller).

methods.name: OnAfterSetupLoad(VRTK_SDKSetup setup)
methods.summary: This method is called just after loading the VRTK_SDKSetup that's using this SDK.

params.value: The SDK Setup which is using this SDK.
